subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Although this new species is similar in the round elevation between the eyes to 

D. pulchellus
Cameron

, it can be easily recognized by the dilated protarsi. This new species is distinguished from its congeners by the combination of the following characters: 
1
) sparsely distributed punctures on head; 
2
) different number of mandible teeth; 
3
) neck with both a dorsal and ventral groove; 
4
) transverse elytra; 
5
) aedeagus large sized and bottle-shaped (

Fig. 
5

E, F); parameres symmetrical and soft, extraordinarily thin and long, curving from ventral to dorsal side (

Fig. 
5
- 
1

E, F).
